An API Gateway is a single entry point that sits in front of backend services and manages, routes, and secures API requests from 
clients.
It’s a key component in microservices architectures.


What an API Gateway Does
Instead of clients calling many services directly:
Client → API Gateway → Microservices


The gateway handles cross-cutting concerns so services stay simple.


Core Responsibilities
1. Request Routing
Routes requests to the correct service

Example:
/users → User Service
/orders → Order Service
-----------------------------------------------------------------
2. Authentication & Authorization
Validates tokens (JWT, OAuth)
Blocks unauthorized requests
Enforces roles and permissions

-----------------------------------------------------------------------
3. Rate Limiting & Throttling
Prevents abuse and DDoS
Limits requests per user or IP

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
4. Load Balancing
Distributes traffic across service instances

--------------------------------------------------------------
5. Request / Response Transformation
Convert protocols (REST ↔ gRPC)
Modify headers or payloads
Aggregate multiple service responses

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6. Caching
Cache frequent responses
Reduce backend load
Improve latency

---------------------------------------------------------------------------
7. Monitoring & Logging
Centralized logs
Metrics and tracing
Error tracking

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Popular API Gateway Solutions
Kong
NGINX API Gateway
AWS API Gateway
Azure API Management
Apigee
Traefik

When to Use an API Gateway
✅ Microservices
✅ Multiple clients (web, mobile, partners)
✅ Security & rate limiting needed
✅ Centralized API management

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Simple Request Flow:
  Client sends request
  Gateway authenticates
  Gateway routes to service
  Service responds
  Gateway returns response
